Space for cognition : gesture and second language learning
################################################################
étude des gestes spontanés
gesturing for thinking pour SLuse of gestures in the form of beats in relation to prsodic features can be a form of enaction -> internalizing the L2 through embodied process
due to mirror neurons -> possible importance of gesture
simulation theory : résonance avec nos états si simulation de l'action
vygotsky : réduction de la syntaxe quand évident
vygotsky : imitation et processus d'internalisation
basic assumption : interconnection (thought, language gesture)
gestures is a means through which linguistic elements (prosody and syllable structure) might be internalized through embodiment.
mcneill : convergence de la pensée, la parole et les gestes à travers "dialogical" interaction
MN : assertion of a semantic overlap btwn gestures and speech
parole procure une structure linéaire et séquentielle à la pensée
gestes apportent éléments synthétiques, holistiques et imagés.
speech emerges from growth point ie the conception of what is communicated
mcneill (2002) : mirror neurons coordinate with language production in the brain
Gesturing for thinking (6 views of embodied cognitin)
mcneill (1992) : iconic gestures cannot help expose releant dimensions of speaker's thought
Mac Neill and Duncan : gestures are typically co-expressive with speech, ie the 2 channels express the same unferlying idea unit but do not necessarily express identical aspects of it

